              <tr><td colspan="3"><b>Description</b><br>
This zone is part of the newly discovered continent of Kunark. Please post any and all information you can about the new zone, including the type of zone (town, dungeon, forest, etc), what are the adjacent zones (location would be nice but not necessary), and it's level range. Also feel free to post any new items, NPC's, or landmarks you come across.<br><br>
<b>Player Comments</b> (total:10, showing:1-5) <a href="JavaScript:popComment('comment.php3?type=zone&tid=85')">add</a><br>
<a href="mailto:Damoen_Wiz@Hotmail.com">Damoen</a> of the Bertox server on May. 05, 2000 at 05:02pm said...<br>
Ah my fovorite dungeon.  To know if you are in Nurga, when you zone in from Frontier Mountains.  You come to a pool of water.  On your right there is a water fall that you can go up and on your left a water fall you can go down.  To go up the waterfall, you must have a small body frame, or be shrank.  If you are of medium build you must have sow to continue up the waterfall.  Now I have explored the dungeon fairly extensively.  The highest level mob I have found was level 36.  This dungeon consists of Goblins, Spiders and Badger people.  I did not see any goblins of level 36.  There were a few spiders and Badgers white at 36.  Hope that helps =)<br><br>
<a href="mailto:ariakas@genglo.com">Langevin</a> of the Hammer server on May. 05, 2000 at 04:38pm said...<br>
Sorry, forgot to add that the dungeon with the pit trap at the entrance is the Temple, not the Mines...  Also, we've found only 3 special items so far, a Gob Parrying Dagger, a Burynai Gi and a Mountain Death Belt.. all good items for newbies.  The Gi is a cleric robe that looks like brown cryosilk (very cool on high elves) and the belt is for small races, AC 8 +25 HP.. <br><br>
<a href="mailto:ariakas@genglo.com">Langevin</a> of the Seventh Hammer server on May. 05, 2000 at 04:31pm said...<br>
Hail!  My group has spent a good deal of time in here.  We haven't seen any "real" named mobs, just specials with different names (cenobite, etc).  The MINES are known as "Nurga" and do connect with the Temple of Droga which is not too far in.  This is the dungeon where the waterfall is near the entrance from Frontier Mtns.  You CAN jump down the waterfall w/out damage, better to lev down.  It's basically a shortcut to an area to one of the pits under the car tracks.  There are blues to 45 way in the back (spiders, tons of burynai), but it's mostly a great place from 30 to 40.  No wanderers and things are spaced out in pairs or in 3s most of the time.  A very easy dungeon to conquer if  you keep moving.  Fast spawns.. Less than 15 minutes.<br><br>
<a href="mailto:tim.smith@omnidssi.com">Torlack</a> of the Luclin server on May. 01, 2000 at 09:45pm said...<br>
Well, a group of low 40s went in this dungeon and we noticed at 40 there is a fair amount of blue mobs, but at 44, mostly green.  We did notice that instead of going down the waterfall, you can swim up.  Don't really know how the two are connected if the even are.<br><br>
<a href="mailto:Siclid@hotmail.com">Siclid</a> on Apr. 30, 2000 at 11:45am said...<br>
Okay, there are *two* mine-like dungeons within the Frontier Mtns. Mines of Nurga and Temple of Droga. It seems the confusion has already begun....<br><br>
